2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
2 tbsp BBQ Sauce
2 unit(s) Artisan Bun
1 unit(s) Red Onion
56 g Spring Mix
1 tbsp Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend
¼ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
1 tbsp Balsamic Vinegar
2 tbsp Italian Breadcrumbs
1 unit(s) Mini Cucumber
1.13 tsp Sugar*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
1.5 tbsp Oil*
0.38 tsp Salt*

Peel, then cut onion into 1/4-inch slices.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then onions. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, 3-4 min.
Add 1 tsp (2 tsp) sugar and season with salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until onions are dark golden-brown, 6-8 min. Stir in half the Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend and half the vinegar.
Transfer onions to a plate, then cover to keep warm.
Carefully rinse and wipe the pan clean.

Heat the same pan over medium. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then Beyond Meat® patties. Pan-fry until cooked through, 4-5 min per side.**
Remove the pan from heat, then transfer patties to one side of an unlined baking sheet.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over patties. Set aside.

Meanwhile, add mayo and half the BBQ sauce (use all for 4ppl)  to a small bowl.
Season with pepper, then stir to combine.

Arrange buns on the other side of the baking sheet with patties, cut-sides up. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, use another unlined baking sheet.)
Toast in the top of the oven until buns are toasted and cheese melts, 3-4 min. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, toast in batches.) (TIP: Keep an eye on buns so they don't burn!)

Meanwhile, Thinly slice cucumber.
Add remaining balsamic vinegar, 1/8 tsp (1/4 tsp) sugar and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil to a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then combine.
Add cucumbers and spring mix, then toss to combine just before serving.

Toss salad to combine.
Spread BBQ mayo onto top and bottom buns.
Stack Beyond Meat® patties and caramelized onions onto bottom buns. Close with top buns.
Divide burgers and salad between plates.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, skip the instructions to form the patties. ( NOTE: Save breadcrumbs and remaining Smoked
Paprika-Garlic Blend for another use.) Cook patties the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the beef. **